    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.0141 Phoenix Group/120</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lindsay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Excellency the British
                    Ambassador and refers to the British Embassy’s <hi rend="italic"
                        >aide-Mémoire</hi> of March 31, 1939 with regard to the draft exchange of
                    notes defining future administration of Canton and Enderbury Islands.</p>
                <p>This Government accepts the verbal amendments proposed by the British Government
                    and proposes that the exchange of notes take place on Thursday, April 6, and
                    that the notes be released for publication on Saturday, April 8, 1939.</p>
                <p>When the time comes for a British company to make use of the facilities
                    established on Canton Island by an American company or companies satisfactory to
                    the United States Government, in pursuance of paragraph VI of the proposed
                    exchange of notes, this Government will be glad to transmit a request for this
                    purpose to such company or companies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-04">April 4,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
